      • registerCleanDependency

        public void registerCleanDependency​(EditorCell cell,
                                    jetbrains.mps.util.Pair<org.jetbrains.mps.openapi.model.SNodeReference,​String> pair)
        Description copied from interface: UpdateSession
        Register "clean" dependency of the editor cell created as a part of this update session on the node's property.

        "clean" dependency type means: this editor cell was created as direct representation of this property and if only this property was changed then corresponding cell should be just synchronized with model

        Specified by:
        registerCleanDependency in interface UpdateSession
        Parameters:
        cell - - editor cell created as a part of this editor update session
        pair - - a pair of node reference and property name

      • updateChildNodeCell

        public EditorCell updateChildNodeCell​(org.jetbrains.mps.openapi.model.SNode node)
        Description copied from interface: UpdateSession
        Should be called as a part of incremental update of EditorCells tree represented inside associated EditorComponent only.

        Can be called to update editor cell for the child node to insert it into constructing cell tree as a child cell.

        This method creates the new cell context with the node location created from node and its SNode.getContainmentLink() and pushes it to the editor cell factory.

        Specified by:
        updateChildNodeCell in interface UpdateSession
        Parameters:
        node - - node to create cell for
        Returns:
        updated EditorCell for the specified node

      • updateAttributeCell

        public EditorCell updateAttributeCell​(AttributeKind attributeKind,
                                      EditorCell attributedCell,
                                      org.jetbrains.mps.openapi.model.SNode attribute)
        Description copied from interface: UpdateSession
        Updating the EditorCell representing some attribute (see AttributeKind). Attributed cell (representing complete node/or property/..) should be already updated and passed as a parameter of this method call.

        The update process for the attribute node may include attributed cell into the constructed tree of editor cells. In this case attributed cell will be accessed by calling UpdateSession.getAttributedCell(AttributeKind, SNode) method.

        Specified by:
        updateAttributeCell in interface UpdateSession
        Parameters:
        attributeKind - - specification of the attribute kind
        attributedCell - - cell representing attributed node/property/..
        attribute - - node representing attribute
        Returns:
        updated EditorCell representing a cell for node/property/reference attribute

      • getAttributedCell

        @NotNull
public EditorCell getAttributedCell​(AttributeKind attributeKind,
                                    org.jetbrains.mps.openapi.model.SNode attribute)
        Description copied from interface: UpdateSession
        May be called to access attributed cell of specified attribute kind while building the cell for the node of attribute. Returned cell is expected to be inserted into sub-tree of EditorCells, created for the node of attribute.

        This method should be called as a sub-sequence of UpdateSession.updateAttributeCell(AttributeKind, EditorCell, SNode) method in order to access second parameter (EditorCell) from there.

        Specified by:
        getAttributedCell in interface UpdateSession
        Parameters:
        attributeKind - - parameter specifying the type of attributed cell to access
        attribute - - node used to create error cell if corresponding attributed cell was not found
        Returns:
        attributed EditorCell or error cell if such cell was not found.
